We need to look at serious ways to strengthen our border security, including passing comprehensive immigration reform that increases funding for innovative surveillance and security technology and more agents at the border.
Tariffs will not secure our border, but they will place a significant financial burden on Iowa farmers, businesses and families.

I strongly encourage the President not to follow through on the threat to escalate tariffs with Mexico. The trade war with China is already devastating Iowa farmers and increasing consumer prices on Iowa families.
